results.name: cq-social-livefyre-pkg
results.description:
This package allows you to integrate Livefyre's industry leading curation capabilities with your AEM instance, allowing you to publish valuable user generated content (UGC) from social networks to your site in minutes. There are 3 different components to this package.

  1. Import UGC Content into AEM Assets:
    • You can import Twitter and Instagram user-generated content (UGC) from Livefyre Studio to AEM Assets using the UGC Importer.
    • Accessing your Livefyre Library.
    • Searching real-time on Twitter and Instagram using Livefyre Social Search.
    • Manage Rights on the UGC.
  2. Add Livefyre Components to AEM Sites or Communities:
    • Instantly build and customize dynamic and engaging experiences using a suite of Social Components including Maps, Galleries, and Media Walls.
    • Publish UGC in AEM Sites or Communities.
  3. Import Product Catalogs into Livefyre with AEM Commerce:
    • AEM Commerce users can seamlessly integrate their existing product catalogue into Livefyre to associated products to specific UGC and drive conversion in their websites. This integration enables AEM customers to deliver shoppable UGC experiences in their sites.
    • Editing or deleting items in your AEM Commerce Product Catalog, automatically update the changes in Livefyre.

For more details about AEM and Livefyre visit:

  • Livefyre documentation
  • Livefyre support

results.name: aemforms-msdynamics-configuration-pkg
results.description: The package bundles an OData cloud service configuration for Microsoft Dynamics 365 and a form data model. The configuration allows you to connect AEM Forms with your Dynamics 365 instance with minimal configuration changes. The form data model is configured to use the Dynamics 365 instance as data source. It lets you create adaptive forms that retrieve data from and submit data to Dynamics 365 entities and services. This package requires Forms add-on package for AEM 6.4 as a prerequisite.

results.name: aemforms-reference-fragments-pkg
results.description: The fragments package contains reusable field fragments that you can use for authoring forms. Each fragment contains a set of unique fields and validation rules. This package highlights the ease with which you can create forms using fragments and accelerate forms development. This package requires Forms add-on package for AEM 6.4 as a prerequisite.

results.name: aemforms-reference-themes-pkg
results.description: The themes package bundles pre-built themes on AEM Forms that you can use on different forms to build consistent form experiences. All input fields, components, and fragments confer to the styles defined in their respective themes. All themes are responsive, optimized for smartphones, tablets, and desktops, and editable using the Theme Editor in AEM Forms. This package requires Forms add-on package for AEM 6.4 as a prerequisite.
